article.headline: Dartmouth 56, Quinnipiac 53
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. (AP) -- Leon Pattman scored 13 of his game-high 19 points in the second half and DeVon Mosley added 13 points as Dartmouth came from behind to beat Quinnipiac 56-53 on Monday. Van Crafton had 12 points and Chris Wehye scored 11 to lead Quinnipiac (2-7), which got a game-high 10 rebounds from Victor Akinyanju off the bench. Dartmouth (3-6), which fell behind 17-4 early and was down seven points with less than eight minutes remaining, was trailing 53-52 with 43 seconds to play after Wehye made the first of two free throws for Quinnipiac. Wehye missed his second shot before Pattman, who grabbed the rebound, was fouled shooting at the other end. He made both free throws to give Dartmouth a 54-53 lead with 19 seconds left. After Alex Barnett forced a Quinnipiac turnover with 3.5 seconds left, Pattman was fouled and made two more free throws for the final margin. Pattman was 8-for-8 from the foul line and 3-for-5 from outside the arc while also leading Dartmouth with seven rebounds.
